def standartization(X): 
    X_mean = X.mean(axis = 0)
    X_std = X.std(axis = 0)
    X_st = (X - X_mean)/X_std
    return X_st

#ridge regression
def ridge_r(X,y,lambda_p):
    n = X.shape[1]
    I = np.eye(n)
    I[0,0] = 0
    X_np = X.to_numpy()
    y_np = y.to_numpy()

    
    beta = np.linalg.inv(X_np.T @ X_np + lambda_p * I) @ X_np.T @ y_np
    return beta

some validation¶

In [320]:
def cv_ridge(X,Y,lambdas): 
    
    kf = KFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=6)
    lambda_errors = {}
    
    for lambda_p in lambdas:
        rmse_list = []
        
        for train, test in kf.split(X):
            X_train, X_test = X.iloc[train], X.iloc[test]
            Y_train, Y_test = Y.iloc[train], Y.iloc[test]          
            beta = ridge_r(X_train, Y_train, lambda_p)
            y_pred = X_test @ beta
            y_pred.columns = ['popularity']
            rmse = np.sqrt(((Y_test - y_pred) ** 2).mean())
            rmse_list.append(rmse)
            
        lambda_errors[lambda_p] = np.mean(rmse_list)
        

    best_lambda = min(lambda_errors, key=lambda_errors.get)
    return best_lambda, lambda_errors
